section.section:
The criteria shall include:
the zoning of the land;
the present and past use of the land including land under the Soil Bank Program of the United States;
the productivity of the land, including timberlands and reforested lands; and
the gross income that is derived from the agricultural activity.

text.section:
In administering this section, periodically, the Director shall consult with:
the Secretary of Agriculture;
officials of the State who are knowledgeable in agriculture;
representatives of the agricultural community;
officials of counties and municipal corporations; and
other persons as determined by the Director.

section.section:
In this subsection the following words have the meanings indicated:
"actively used" means land that is actually and primarily used for a continuing farm or agricultural use;
"agricultural land unit" means the combination of not more than 3 parcels of land when the parcels are:
located in the same county; and
under the same ownership;
"average gross income" means the average of the 2 highest years of gross income during a 3-year period;
"family farm unit" means not more than 1 parcel of land of less than 20 acres for each immediate family member for land that is:
contiguous to land receiving the farm or agricultural use assessment; and
owned by a member or members of the immediate family of the owner of the farm or agricultural use land; and
"gross income" means the actual income that is received in a calendar year that results directly from the farm or agricultural use of the land.

If land that appears to be actively used does not yield an average gross income of $2,500, the Director shall waive the gross income requirement on finding that:
the land is leased and the nature of the farm or agricultural use of the land when related to the amount of the land in farm or agricultural use reasonably would be expected to yield an average gross income of at least $2,500;
the nature of the farm or agricultural use of the land and the amount of the land in farm or agricultural use reasonably would be expected to yield an average gross income of at least $2,500 from the agricultural products, if sold, that are derived from the use of the land;
a drought or other natural cause has adversely affected the income-producing capability of the land during a 3-year period; or
for a newly established farm or agricultural use, the nature of the use and the amount of the land in farm or agricultural use reasonably would be expected to yield an average gross income of at least $2,500 if the use had existed for a 3-year period.

Subject to paragraph (2) of this subsection, the following land does not qualify to be assessed under this section:
land rezoned to a more intensive use than the use that immediately preceded the rezoning, if a person with an ownership interest in the land has applied for or requested the rezoning;
land used as a homesite, which means the area of land that is reasonably related to a dwelling;
parcels of land of less than 3 acres that are under the same ownership excluding the homesite unless:
the land is owned by an owner of adjoining land that is receiving the farm or agricultural use assessment and is actively used;
the owner receives at least 51% of the owner's gross income from the active use; or
the parcels are part of a family farm unit;
if part of a subdivision plat, parcels of land of less than 10 acres that are owned by an owner of 5 other parcels of land of less than 10 acres each that are located in the same county and that are receiving the farm or agricultural use assessment;
parcels of woodland of less than 5 acres excluding the homesite; or
land that fails to meet the gross income requirement of subsection (g) of this section.

The Director may grant a waiver from the requirements of subsection (e) or (g) of this section if:
the property owner is at least 70 years of age;
the property owner applies to the Department for a waiver of the requirements of either subsection (e) or (g) of this section;
the land has not changed ownership during the two previous 3-year cycles; and
the land has been assessed for at least the two previous 3-year cycles on the basis of farm or agricultural use under the law or regulations of the Department that were in effect as of the date of the application.

The Director may grant a waiver from the requirements of subsection (e) or (g) of this section if:
the property owner becomes disabled and is unable to continue the farm or agricultural use of the land;
the property owner applies to the Department for a waiver of the requirements of either subsection (e) or (g) of this section;
the property owner engaged in farm or agricultural use activities on the land prior to the disability; and
the land has been assessed for at least the two previous 3-year cycles on the basis of farm or agricultural use under the law or regulations of the Department that were in effect as of the date of the application.
